article.description: Nathan Knight recorded 15 points and 12 rebounds to lift William & Mary to an 88-61 win over Hofstra on Thursday night.
article.headline: Knight's double-double sends William & Mary past Hofstra
article.linkText: Knight's double-double sends William & Mary past Hofstra
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- Nathan Knight recorded 15 points and 12 rebounds to lift William & Mary to an 88-61 win over Hofstra on Thursday night. Andy Van Vliet had 18 points for William & Mary (10-5, 2-0 Colonial Athletic Conference). Luke Loewe added 12 points. Tyler Hamilton had six rebounds for the visitors. William & Mary dominated the first half and led 45-23 at the break. The Pride's 23 points in the first half marked a season low for the team. Eli Pemberton had 15 points for the Pride (11-5, 2-1), whose five-game win streak came to end. Jalen Ray added 11 points. Isaac Kante had 11 points and 10 rebounds. William & Mary matches up against Northeastern on the road on Saturday. Hofstra matches up against Elon at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
